    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="721" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d721">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received Jan. 20.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 758.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In connection with my No. 703, of December
                            3, I have the honor to transmit herewith for your further information
                            copy of a dispatch <pb facs="0712" n="1446" xml:id="pg_1446"/> from the
                            British consul at Erzeroum to the British ambassador, relating to the
                            position of the American missionaries at Bitlis.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 758.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cumberbatch</persName>
                                    to Sir <persName type="to">Philip Currie</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Erzeroum</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-16">
                                <hi rend="italic">December 16,
                                        1895</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 312.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my dispatch No. 289,
                                of the 25th ultimo, I have the honor to report, for the information
                                of the United States minister, that Her Majesty’s vice consul at Yan
                                informs me that Dr. Reynolds has returned to that place, but that
                                the American missionaries in Bitlis have decided to remain in the
                                latter town for the present, in the hope of a change for the better,
                                though their position is very unpleasant, especially that of Mr. G.
                                Knapp, who, though he has a strong guard on his premises, has not
                                been able to venture outside his house since the massacres, as it
                                appears that the vali and the Moslem population are still greatly
                                excited against the Christians, and especially against him.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">H. A. Cumberbatch.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
